Well, I am a necro and I always offer to give the mana back (and, when in level range, to assist the group TPer or Rezer is in during a few minutes, to compensate the absence and/or the temporary lost of mana). Believe me or not, very often these nice peoples refuse the mana and the assistance and wish me a good hunt ...<br>
I had to pay to get a TP, but it was a minority of cases. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/usortilegewolfsoul.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sortilege Wolfsoul</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Regular Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/9/01 11:37:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=221.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Always pay for TP and ress?</span><hr size=1> ooops posted before I was finished <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
