People don't give donations to Paladins they are not grouped with who use Lay Hands on them. Every time they use that, they have to wait an EQ day [1.5 hours] before it can be used again. Hudge downtime, and if it is being used - it probably saved someone's life. Someone who would otherwise be looking for a rez.<br>
<br>
What about those really cool rogues and monks who drag corpses from groups that they are not even in. If you think about it, those people are putting their character at death risk. As far as I know, they don't get donations for dragging bodies.<br>
<br>
What about that ranger in the zone who you want to babysit tracking for the next 4 or 5 hours to keep an eye out for your uber mob of phat lewtiness? Especially considering that if the ranger does it, you're probably going to benefit financial and he could have easily told his group or someone else to go after it.<br>
<br>
If you yell for help and some people show up to save you, do you donate to your saviours? What if one of them dies? Do you donate to the cleric that is willing to rez that person?<br>
